summary: 'The Old Sage' by Jed Henry.  12″ x 17″ giclee print on Acid-free handmade Japanese paper in a signed edition for $40. The white...
caption:
‘The Old Sage’ by Jed Henry.

12″ x 17″ giclee print on Acid-free handmade Japanese paper in a signed edition for $40.

The white cartouche reads:
闇父の如く速き易き道を選ぶのなら、邪悪の代行となるべし

Which roughly translates to:
“If you choose the quick and easy path, you will become an agent of evil”

On sale now from his website.

summary: What was it like working on Rocketman?
question: What was it like working on Rocketman?
answer:
Obviously I can’t say anything because of contracts but know this:

I’ve worked a week on ‘Star Wars’, two weeks/two separate years on 'Fantastic Beasts’, and one day on 'Rocketman’. I haven’t stopped thinking/talking about that one day. It was magical & amazing, I seriously cannot wait for its release.

title: Praxeum-Ship Alderaan’s Sun
body:
Since it seems I have to seriously rest my wrist for at least a few days, I might take the time to introduce you to a small Star Wars project I am currently working on together with a few of my friends!

The Praxeum-Ship of the Jedi-Order started its journey in 1012 BBY and had it’s origins and home base in the Alderaan System, where it spend the first 10 years of its existence until it was taken under command by Yusoik Kav.

The following centuries the Alderaan’s Sun travelled through the outer tim and wild space regions and was a home and place to study for many Jedi-Knights and Jedi-Padawan.

In 92 BBY the ship was taken over my the Jedi-Master Mareè. During the Clone Wars and Order 66 the Alderaan’s Sun spend the majority of its time in the Wild Space. The signal to return ‘home’ did reached them but during their longer journey back to the core another call from a survivor of the purge reached them, convincing them to turn around and flee into Wild Space. They shortly lost contact to that person after and spend the following couple of years cruising around the Outer Rim, looking for and taking in other surviving Jedi and hiding from the empire.

In 11 BBY they started to help out different rebel organisations against the empire, providing them wit supplies before continuing their journey, always being on a hide-and-seek hunt with the empire.

As of 0 BBY the Alderaan’s Sun is on its on-going flee from the empire in the Outer Rim, regulary diving into the Wild Space as well.

This project is way from completly worked out yet and I am very excited to more with the Alderaan’s Sun and it’s crew.

I will maybe open the Alderaan’s Sun for a few more people to join as I always love interacting with different peoples characters and the Alderaan’s sun can definitly use a couple more members in the future!
